<html>
<title>JS Numbers</title>
<body>
<h1 style=text-align:center>JS Number</h1>
<p>The max safe int is</p>
<script>
let x=Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER;
document.write(x)
</script>
<p>This gives the negative infinity</p>
<script>
let y=Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY;
document.write(y)
</script>
<p>This gives postive infinity</p>
<script>
let z=Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY;
document.write(z)
</script>
<p>This gives the exponential value</p>
<script>
let no=4.8;
let n=no.toExponential();
document.write(n)
</script>
<p>This converts num to string</p>
<script>
let num=23;
let txt=num.toString();
document.write(txt)
</script>
<p>This gives the precised num</p>
<script>
let a=12.54832;
let b=a.toPrecision(4);
document.write(b)
</script>
</body>
